runs.comm: on target straightaway, cramps him up for room and he pushes it back to the bowler
that's a late evening slash, Asif's very very generous with his width, short as well, Watson sends that flying over the slips, see you later
good comeback,he gets the ball to nip back and he chops it down towards slip
reckless slash outside the off stump, seems to be in a hurry to move on
in the air and right in the middle of two fielders! He doesn't fully control the pull and short fine leg runs back, but Nazir dives forward and collects it from the deep
tucks it to the on side and retains the strike
gets away with a delivery down the leg side on his pads, tries to work it away but the ball rolls to the keeper off his pads
gets beside the line and steers him just wide of first slip
super way to get off the mark, Naved errs by pitching it full and giving him width, he chops it hard onto the ground and the ball races past the covers
holds the length back and he taps it back to the bowler

super throw from the deep and the third umpire has a look, Warner latches on to the width outside off and slices it in the air just over backward point, Umar Akmal runs back from cover point, slides and fires a flat throw to the keeper, Watson wasn't quick enough on the third run
whoopsy! Clarke slips at the the crease as he whips it away to the on side and he's on all fours, watch out for the stumps, Pup
shuffles and clips him down to the on side
too wide outside off, gentle pace too, he has enough time to roll his wrists and push it away effortlessly wide of backward point
pushes it down the track and tells his partner to wait
almost an action replay, Clarke gets forward a bit too early and he hits it back to the bowler
angles towards the pads and he calls for the second run the minute the ball beats midwicket
clips it away off his pads again wide of midwicket
ungainly shot by Warner, makes room and the ball flies off the toe of the bat and just drops short of Asif at third man
picks the slower ball a little too late and he lunges forward and pushes it towards mid-off
drifts on the pads and he works it to the on side
plays his favourite shot - the pull - it travels flat and quick but there's cover at deep square leg
slower ball clipped wide of square leg, he has to hurry back for the second and the throw is pretty much on target but the bowler fumbles and clips the bails with his hands instead
plays a short-arm pull down to deep square leg
shuffles across his stumps early and deliberately clips him wide of square leg
excellent running, he drops the ball in front of cover and calls immediately, puts pressure on the infield
That's a Warner special! He latches on to a short of a length delivery and just whams it over deep midwicket, he's caught but by the spectator over the fence, somebody give him a VB! It's on me
gets a leading edge to the off side and he hurries the single
tries to play it down to third man but he misses it
makes room bur checks his shot and ends up chopping it wide of cover
grants him width and he slices it wide of point, Gul charges across from third man and mops up
opportunity missed by Pakistan! Clarke drops it towards extra cover and takes a big risk, he looked in real danger of being run out but Khalid Latif's throw at the bowler's end cleared Mt Everest
goes for an ungainly heave but the ball drops in the middle of nowhere in the deep on the off side
width again and he gets a thick outside edge this time to third man
makes room and squirts it wide of cover point for a single
stays beside the line and pushes it wide of cover and calls immediately
lovely delivery, Clarke is very circumspect as he gets forward to drive and the late movement beats the outside edge
gets to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to mid-off
Dropped Stiff chance, Warner swings at a slow delivery and Asif is a bit late to react, the ball deflects off his fingers to long-on
fell for the trap! Warner makes a lot of room to crash that over the off side, the ball is there to be hit but he doesn't spot the fielder Imran Nazir at deep point, easy catch
on the pads and he clips it down to square leg for a single
lot of intent there, he uses his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball and plays an exquisite airborne drive over the covers, the fielder in the deep had no chance
steps down and turns it towards mid-on
gives him width but he ends up chopping it down to point
squirts it behind square on the off side but the running is good, complete the second easily
chops it towards short third man and sets off immediately
shuffles and clips it behind square on the on side for a single
top edges the pull and it falls safe! Hussey isn't in control of that shot and the fielder from deep square charges forward
pushes it towards backward point and sets off, Fawad does really well to slide and save another run, good cricket all round
edges it to the pads and the ball rolls to cover and he risks the single,  the throw was wide

good reflexes! Clarke gets slightly forward and beside the line to slash it away over the off side, but Fawad is alert at point and cups his hands behind that screamer, he kept his eyes on the ball which was like a bolt of lightning
full on the off stump and he pushes it towards mid-off
bowls it short but down the leg side
gets forward and pushes it just wide of backward point
flatter delivery and he pushes it with the turn down to long-on
stays back and pushes it down to mid-off
gets forward and pushes it through the line to long-on
punches it to the off side for a single
gets to the pitch of it and pushes it to long-on
slow and wide outside off and chopped down to cover
full and swinging in, he pushes it through the line to Asif at long-off
drops it shorter, gets it to nip back in and nearly slices him in half, the ball hits his hips and rolls to the off side
full on the off stump and he gently pushes it down to long-off
short and drifting on the body, he shuffles and clips him to the on side

fabulous cricket from Pakistan! Gul catches White all at sea with a short delivery, the ball lobs off White's body and lobs to Fawad at point, Gul thinks White got some glove on it and they go up for the catch, but an unsettled and dazed White ambles out of his crease and an alert Fawad fires the throw at the stumps at White's end, the third umpire takes a look
full on the pads and he works him down to long-on, first runs in Australia colours
forgettable debut in the end for Birt, Malik comes round the wicket and fires it flat on the stumps, Birt goes a long way across and tries to paddle it away, the ball crashes on to leg and middle
defends with soft hands and the ball nearly dribbles back to his stumps
gets forward and drives back to the bowler
gets forward and drives him down to long-off
gets beside the line and steers him to the off side

it's a wide down the leg side and Pakistan aren't complaining at all! Cleverly bowled, fires it down the leg side on seeing Haddin come down the pitch, Kamran does well to follow the line and whip off the bails, he's a long way out
gets off the mark with a clip down to square leg
meanwhile his namesake pinches a single to point
gets forward and pushes it through the line to long-on
sower through the air and he rocks back and cuts to sweeper cover
quicker one, gets turn and bounce, Hussey nearly chops it onto his stumps
knocks it behind square leg
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives him down to long-on
makes room to cut but misses
lot of confidence in that shot! He chips down the track early and carves him over extra cover, bisects 2 fielders in the deep
shuffles and clips him behind square on the on side
that goes rows back! Hussey chips down the track, gets his high backlift down on the ball and lofts with the turn, lands several rows over wide long-on
taps it towards extra cover and sets off very quickly, has to dive at the crease
swings at it outside off and fails to connect
slower yorker and he does well to whips it away past square leg
full on the stumps and pushed to long-on

the slower ball from hell! That was actually a googly! Naved foxes Smith who doesn't quite know whether to play at it or not, the ball cuts back in and slices him in half, he won't want to see a replay of that
fires it quicker and the ball skids onto his pads
squeezes it out to third man and he has to hurry for the single, the throw is wide
full on the off stump and driven to mid-off
speeds past the outside edge, phew that was close
tries to heave it to the on side and nearly chops it onto his stumps, very nearly the 8th wicket there
skids through and he pushes it to the off side
full on the off stump and he drives to the off side
it gets worse for Australia! Another terrific delivery, Gul bangs it in really short and it's a snorter, Johnson desperately sways backward to evade it and the ball brushes his glove, Kamran knows it
low full toss and he clips it down to deep midwicket
oh nice stuff! Gul errs by dropping it short and giving him width, Hussey backs away and times the cut really well, beats third man

brilliant fielding! Pakistan where were you all this while? The batsman pounds it down the ground and Naved at long-on sprints to his left and just manages to pull it back, that looked an obvious four
full on the pads and squeezed out to the on side
full on the pads and he clips it to square leg
tossed up on the pads and worked to the on side
outside edge beats slip, puts pressure on nazir at third man, good running by Hussey to get back for the third
not so good running this time! Hussey rocks back and pulls a slower short delivery, mixup in the running and Umar fires the throw to the bowler's end, he's gone by a mile
fires that in very quick and he pushes it back to the bowler
take that! Hussey steps down the pitch on seeing the flight and carts that long and high over wide long-on
does well to squeeze out a fast yorker, he risks a single to Fawad at point and the throw was just wide, he was a goner otherwise
backs away from  his crease and Gul does well to bowl the bouncer, Hussey swishes at thin air
circumspect running again, squeezes it out to the off side and the throw to the bowler's end is wide
easy catch for Alam this time, Tait gets forward to a pitched up delivery and ends up spooning it straight to point
